reviews.review:
An extremely beautiful execution of what a sequel must/can be, Portal 2 has almost everything:
- Perfect Story to continue the previous game but here they give more details about the background events in a amazing manner without bothering the player too much;
- Fitting music and sounds that accompany the game with delight;
- Interesting and sufficiently lore-filled new characters that develop through the game in an well executed manner;
- New mechanics to make the game feel fresh without messing with the main gameplay ones which makes the game simple and fun;
- Difficulty near perfect (not too challenging to make it annoying but not too easy to lack the feeling of achievement);
- Amazing Coop campaign so you can have fun with a friend while you must work out together to finish your goals;
- Considering the price it's cheap on sale but the normal price isn't that bad at all considering you still have the time challenges and mods to fit for more content.
It's so hard not to love it, almost everything is well made and freshly made.
9.3/10 - [b]highly recommendable[/b]

Ps: GLaDOS is certainly on my favorite characters list, she's just perfect!
